The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Patil, Robin bag coaches posts

Thiruvananthapuram: Sandip Patil and Robin Singh have been appointed coaches of the India A and B teams for the Challenger Series for NKP Salve Trophy scheduled to be held in Mohali from October 10 to 13. 

Along with coach Greg Chappell, the senior team would be assisted by physiotherapist John Gloster, BCCI secretary S. K. Nair said in a release on Thursday. 

Vaibhav Daga and S. Mutthu Kumar would be the physiotherapists for the India A and B teams, respectively. 

The board had decided to avail the services of Ian Frazer sports scientist for the Indian cricket team till the conclusion of the South African tour to India, the release said. (PTI) 




